    "<p>Philanthropist and benefactor of the arts; nephew of art historian <a href=\"/warburga\">Aby M. Warburg</a>; briefly taught art history at Bryn Mawr.": [],
    "Warburg was the youngest of five children of philanthropist Felix Warbug (1871-1937), a partner in the investment firm of Kuhn, Loeb & Company and brother of the German art historian <a href=\"/warburga\">Aby M. Warburg</a>.": [
