    "Warburg funded much of the American Ballet on his own; it was on Warburg's estate that George Balanchine's first ballet created in American was performed.": [],
    "Warburg continued his activity as an art collector, acquiring works by Picasso, Matisse, Hopper, O'Keeffe, Lachaise, Klee, Miro, Brancusi and Calder.": [
